@startuml stip-failover
title Standing in for the backend during an outage

actor "Customer\nat the terminal" as customer
participant "Card terminal\n(gRPC client)" as client
participant "Ingress + Router\n(debit-card-api.local)" as router
participant "regular body\n(talks to backend)" as regular
participant "stip body\n(stands in)" as stip
database "Backend\n(authorisation)" as backend

== Normal operation: activeVariant = regular ==
customer -> client : tap card
client -> router : CreatePayment
router -> regular : route
regular -> backend : authorise
backend --> regular : approved
regular --> client : payment created
client --> customer : approved

== Backend outage (maintenance / bad Friday deploy) ==
regular -> backend : authorise
backend --> regular : timeout / error
note over regular: customers would start seeing errors here

== One command flips the body: activeVariant = stip ==
note over router: helm upgrade --reuse-values --set activeVariant=stip
customer -> client : tap card
client -> router : CreatePayment
router -> stip : route (same contract, same address)
stip --> client : STIP payment created
client --> customer : approved (never noticed)
@enduml
